    <FAQSection slot="faqs">
      <FAQ question="Why is automating workflows in a business important?" checked="checked">
        Workflow automation primarily enhances efficiency by streamlining processes, reducing manual errors, and saving
        time. It also leads to cost savings, improves productivity, and allows staff to focus on more strategic tasks
        instead of repetitive activities.
      </FAQ>
      <FAQ question="How does automating workflows impact employee productivity?">
        Automating routine and time-consuming tasks frees up employees to focus on higher-value work that requires
        creative and strategic thinking. This not only increases productivity but also often results in higher job
        satisfaction and engagement.
      </FAQ>
      <FAQ question="How can automation enhance business decision-making?">
        Automated workflows typically involve data collection and analysis. This allows businesses to access real-time
        data and insights, facilitating informed and timely decision-making. It ensures that decisions are grounded in
        data rather than intuition.
      </FAQ>
      <FAQ question="Is workflow automation helpful for small and medium-sized businesses?">
        Yes, medium-sized businesses can benefit significantly from workflow automation. It helps level the playing
        field with larger competitors by enabling them to operate more efficiently, react quickly to market changes, and
        manage resources more effectively.
      </FAQ>
      <FAQ question="Does workflow automation require a major overhaul of existing processes?">
        Not necessarily. While some businesses may choose to undergo a complete overhaul, workflow automation can also
        be implemented gradually. Many solutions are flexible and can be integrated with current processes, enabling a
        smoother transition and scalability.
      </FAQ>
      <FAQ question="How does NLP contribute to data-driven decision-making?">
        NLP contributes by turning unstructured language data into structured, actionable insights. This helps
        businesses understand customer sentiments, market trends, and operational inefficiencies, leading to more
        informed decision-making.
      </FAQ>
    </FAQSection>
